<br>
-If you believe the landings were faked, maybe you can answer the following questions:<br>
<br>
I will.<br>
<br>
1) Who was NASA trying to fool? Russia? Russia (and just about every country on Earth) could track the Apollo spacecraft all the way to the moon using radar and by tracking Apollo's radio transmissions. Even amateur HAM radio operators could track Apollo using relatively cheap equipment. There is no way to trick Russia into believing Apollo went to the moon if it really didn't.<br>
<br>
They bounced the transmissions off the moon. We've been doing this for years.<br>
<br>
2) Where did the Apollo spacecraft go if not to the moon? People saw the rockets launch, so we know they at least went into Earth orbit. Any object as big as Apollo can be seen from the ground with just the naked eye. That means the Russians could have seen the Apollo pass overhead if it stayed in Earth orbit.<br>
<br>
One of the few questions we're unsure of. There are a few possiblilites:<br>
<br>
a.Apollo's mission was to find signs of extraterrestrial life on the Moon, which NASA already suspected. They did, and so used the 'backup' films to cover it up to the public, who they deemed not ready.<br>
<br>
b.NASA launched a rocket, empty. They knew the rocket would burn up in the Van Allen belts, and so they wouldnt worry about it. This is what I believe to be true.<br>
<br>
3) The astronauts returned over 840lbs. of moon rock to Earth. Moon rocks are unique and can not be found on Earth and can not be faked. The rocks from the moon are billions of years old and yet they have never been exposed to oxygen or water. They have been exposed to direct radiation from the sun as well as micrometeor impacts. So I ask, how did NASA fake the moon rocks?<br>
<br>
Is this fact, or something NASA told you? I dont believe you've SEEN the moon rocks, you just assume what NASA says is true. Actually, NASA refused to let the rocks be analyzed.<br>
<br>
4) Over 400,000 people worked on the Apollo program. How can that many people keep such a huge secret?<br>
<br>
The key word- they DIDN'T. Dark Moon calls these people 'Whistle-Blowers', who attempted to show to us the truth of the matter while not revealing what they did to NASA. Whistle-Blowers such as these allowed the shadow descrepancies to pass in the photos and other problems.<br>
<br>
5) Every second of every mission to the moon can be accounted for. There are audio and video recordings, photographs, and transcripts of everything the astronauts ever said or did during their missions. How could NASA fake all of that?<br>
<br>
..o.o; This is the easiest to answer. Its just like a movie. They had a script written out, and they recorded it there. It's really the photos that have the most problems. Ever seen the picture of the 'C' rock from Apollo 16? A rock with the letter 'C' written clearly on it, and the same 'C' on the ground. Perfect for the propmaster of the set. Plus, this C was airbrushed out in later pictures...why do that if it wasn't authentic?<br>
<br>
6) Why would NASA fake the moon landings in the first place? What would they gain from it? The consequences of a failed hoax would be far too serious to justify it. If a hoax was discovered the reputation of the US government would go down the toilet and America would become a joke for the rest of time. So why would they risk that just to trick Russia into believing they went to the moon?<br>
<br>
Easy-power. The Americans became the first ones to make it to the moon, which put the notion into everyone's heads that America had superior technology, when in fact it didn't. It was also during the Cold War, where America and the Soviets were locked in bitter conflict for superiority.<br>
<br>
